    "created_at": "2023-01-06T09:33:14Z",
    "updated_at": "2023-01-06T09:33:14Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hi @micieslak , @alexandraB99 confirmed with the design team that the following rules should apply to these components.\r\n\r\n1) Where there is a primary CTA such as 'Add', this should be augmented with the number of items selected if that CTA is directly related to the application/sending/submission etc of the selected items. So in the top component example, selecting a checklist item should result in +1 being appended to the 'Add' label.. For example, if the user selects 1 item, the button label should read 'Add 1'. The count on the button should increase/decrease based on checklist item selection/deselection. This is important as it clarifies to the user how many selections they currently have when some/all of those selections might be out of view due to scrolling of the list / searching.\r\n\r\n2) Selected items should only be shown when the user is searching the list if there are matching strings in that value. If not, those selected items should be hidden until the search is changed to include matching strings or cleared.\r\n\r\nHope that helps, any further questions on that just shout. We can add creating flows for these components to our list if helpful - just let us know. \r\n\r\ncc @John-44 @xAlisher ",
